\section*{PHLEBOTOMY:}

The donor should be greeted cheerfully and should be assisted to the phlebotomy bed. The room should be a peaceful, pleasant and cool one.

\section*{PROCEDURE:}

Always confirm the serial number of the pint and donors card sample tube and vice versa.
1. Sterilise the vein puncture site, after it has been prepared nothing should be touched to this area except the needle.
2. Select the best vein for the sterilised area and unless the veins of donors are visible, apply a tourniquet or blood pressure cuff to the donor upper arm and inflate to $50-60 \mathrm{mmHg}$ and instruct the donor to open and close the first.
3. Immediately do the phlebotomy without delay.
4. After phlebotomy, tape the needle and place sterile gauze over it. Donor must never be left unattended during donation. Should take approx. 9 minutes
5. Mix blood and anticoagulant gently, frequently enough to prevent coagulation.
6. If the blood is adequate, this can be determined by either weighing the pint or apply pressure, the pint should never be too hard or flappy.

After collection:
i. = Heat seal the tube, apply a knot or put a clip. (metal clip with a hand sealer)
ii. = Apply gentle pressure on the punctured site in the thumb using a sterile gauze.
iii. = Tell the donor to raise his arm and elbow kept straight and to hold the gauze firmly on the punctured site in his other hand.
iv. = Another seal should be made near the beg.
v. = Recheck the blood pint number and the donors card again and refrigerate the unit immediately either in a special blood transportation box with enough ice packs (should not go $>10^{0} \mathrm{C}$ during transportation) or in a refrigerator at $2-4^{0} \mathrm{C}$.

\section*{INSTRUCTION TO BLOOD DONORS AFTER PHLEBOTOMY:}
1. The donor should lie at least for 10 minutes.
2. Drink more fluids than usual for the next few hours and have a good meal 24 hrs .
3. In case of any bleeding from the puncture, should apply pressure with the finger to stop it.
4. Should he/she feel faint or dizzy after leaving the bed, should sit down immediately and put head between knees or lie with head lower than the rest of the body until the dizziness stops.
5. Donor should avoid strenuous activities for the next 24 -hrs e.g. playing football.
6. Should not donate again for the next $3 / 4$ months.

